social_posts.post_text: It’s been a long development process!!! Here’s a preview 🌈🦄🎂🧁🏺💕#ceramicvase #cakevase #rainbow #colorfulart #oneofakind

Today is my half birthday! I can't believe I'm already halfway through the year 🎂It's been a great 6 months so far, I have not posted much ceramic updates lately because I have been focusing on my design projects. I've accomplished a lot in the past six months 🙌 I'm especially excited about finishing the Google UX Design Professional Certification ✨❣️And I just returned from an epic trip to Maui where I swam with the biggest green turtles ever🐢I'm so grateful for all the good things that have happened to me in the past year and looking forward to the challenges that the second half of the year will bring 💪I'm excited to learn and grow, and I'm ready to take on whatever comes my way.
I'm so grateful for all the people in my life who love and support me 🥰I couldn't ask for a better family and friends. I hope you all are having a wonderful weekend 🌅
Back in the studio working on some experiments with color sprays and drips, I think I'm pretty pleased so far 💕✨❣️💗🦄🌈 #ceramicart #porcelain #stoneware #sugarskull #skull

I'm back in the studio again! I've missed the feeling of having my hands in clay and the satisfaction of seeing a new piece of art come to life. Stay tuned for regular updates! I'm also excited to share my journey with all of you.

Video footage courtesy of studio mate @kimon_soko

#art #comeback #creativity #inspiration #newbeginnings #porcelain #sculpture #contemporaryceramics #artcomeback #creativejourney #rekindledpassion #artneverdies #deathbysugar

👋 Hi, I am Jacqueline Tse, AKA “Mad Brooklyn.” I design and make art objects to put a smile on your face. 

🍦I am addicted to sugar! This love/hate relationship inspires most of what you see here on this website.

🍭I think colorful confections are the highest form of art. Let’s celebrate it by immortalizing it in ceramics (or at least a thousand years!)

⚒️ I sculpt everything, including all molds used in the process are made by me.

👩🏻 I am Chinese American. I was born in San Jose, California and spent my childhood between the bay area and Hong Kong.

🏜️ After 18 years in New York City, I am now living a slower paced life and work out of a peaceful home studio in Tucson, Arizona.

🥰Thank you for checking out my content here! Feel free to comment, DM, or send me an email and let me know what you would like to see more of, I’d love to hear from you💕

📸 By @ericmichaelpearson

I will be teaching a workshop @the.ceramic.school’s 🌐 "Ceramics Congress" Nov 17-19th, 2023 😍it’s an online pottery festival  🎉 with 72 hours of workshops! My workshop will be on how to make the perfect porcelain slip to decorate your ceramics like a pastry chef 👩‍🍳🎂🧁🍰
